node.text:
I answered some questions a while back, in collaboration with @ultrahuman_official, on how motherhood has changed my life for the better! What a wild and epic ride we’re all on! Enjoy 😊 

Check the link in my bio for an exciting offer on the Ultrahuman app.

#Motherhood #Mothersday #Mentalstrength #endurance #strength #fitness #fit #crossfit #fittestmum #Ultrahuman #IAmUltrahuman #fitnessgoals #fitnessmotivation

node.text:
I’ll never be here to tell anyone how to do anything. I’m here making mistakes and correcting them, and then sharing my story with anyone listening. If we all shared experiences rather than pushed opinions and agendas, or in the name of fame and recognition, imagine how far we could all grow together 🥰 New mummas in all your postpartum glory, you’re badass, don’t ever think otherwise!! That kid looking up at you thinks you’re the entire world. 

Happy Monday ✌🏽

Posted @withregram • @crossfitgames An Encouraging Message to New Mothers From 2017 Second-Fittest Woman on Earth @karasaundo 🇦🇺 🔊

Eight-time CrossFit Games athlete and mother Kara Saunders shares what she’d do differently in the postpartum period if she were to do it all over again. Saunders emphasizes recovery, nutrition, and consistency as important things to focus on. 

Saunders finished eighth at the 2020 CrossFit Games. This year, she finished third worldwide in the CrossFit Open and took second in Oceania during the Quarterfinal this past weekend. 

Visit Saunders’ YouTube page to follow her journey through motherhood and fitness.
—
#CrossFitGames #CrossFitMum #Fitness #CrossFit #Workout #CrossFitTraining #CrossFitKids #Inspiration #CrossFitWomen 🎥 @wykieetsebeth

Happy New Year to you all ✌🏽

node.text:
I really love good food but man do I hate shopping!

Anyone else living for buying everything online right now or is it just me? If it can’t be delivered to me in the comfort of my home gym then I don’t want it 🙅🏽‍♀️😂

🥩 @ourcowau every single month!

node.text:
My happy place when I have more time 🥦🫑🥒 Mum was a chef when I was a kid so I’ve always loved cooking but in season I don’t get too creative because I’m so tired and busy most of the time.
Nutrition is a real passion of mine though and I truly believe it’s the single most powerful and one of the main things we can actually control, to take charge of your health!
This is where I’ll be for the off-season….and at the beach 🥰🙌🏽
